Dialogue: 2,0:17:55.52,0:17:57.12,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}It has our company's stamp on it
Dialogue: 3,0:18:04.76,0:18:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}有个白痴在结算时把我们的股票卖给了我们
Dialogue: 2,0:18:04.76,0:18:07.60,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Some idiot has sold us our shares at the time of settlement
Dialogue: 3,0:18:16.24,0:18:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Grindlays!
Dialogue: 2,0:18:16.24,0:18:17.28,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Grindlays!
Dialogue: 3,0:18:18.40,0:18:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}我们应该抓住这个把柄
Dialogue: 2,0:18:18.40,0:18:19.88,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}[Ashwin] 'Let's catch Grindlays by the balls'
Dialogue: 3,0:18:20.72,0:18:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}告诉他们留着他们的钱归还我们的股份
Dialogue: 2,0:18:20.72,0:18:24.04,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}tell them to keep their money and return our shares
Dialogue: 3,0:18:25.44,0:18:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}不
Dialogue: 2,0:18:25.44,0:18:26.24,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}No
Dialogue: 3,0:18:27.52,0:18:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}不是Grindlays干的，这是熊队的游戏
Dialogue: 2,0:18:27.52,0:18:29.12,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}This is not Grindlays It's the bears' game
Dialogue: 3,0:18:29.96,0:18:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}如果我们需要解决什么人，那就是熊
Dialogue: 2,0:18:29.96,0:18:31.84,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}If there's someone we need to tackle, it's the bears
Dialogue: 3,0:18:31.96,0:18:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}什么意思？
Dialogue: 2,0:18:31.96,0:18:32.84,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Meaning?
Dialogue: 3,0:18:33.52,0:18:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}如果我们和 Grindlays 谈
Dialogue: 2,0:18:33.52,0:18:34.88,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}If we talk to Grindlays
Dialogue: 3,0:18:35.40,0:18:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}熊会立刻得到我们的信息
Dialogue: 2,0:18:35.40,0:18:38.08,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}the bears will immediately get information, that we know
Dialogue: 3,0:18:40.76,0:18:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}现在不是防御的时候，而是进攻的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:18:40.76,0:18:42.68,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}This isn't the time to defend but to attack
Dialogue: 3,0:18:44.08,0:18:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}在接下来的两个月里，让那些看空者尽可能多地抛售股票吧
Dialogue: 2,0:18:44.08,0:18:47.12,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Let those bears hammer as many shares as they want, for the next two months
Dialogue: 3,0:18:48.32,0:18:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}他们应该会觉得我们没有资金了
Dialogue: 2,0:18:48.32,0:18:50.04,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}They should feel we are out of funds
Dialogue: 3,0:18:51.72,0:18:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}然后，在适当的时候，我再把股价抬上去
Dialogue: 2,0:18:51.72,0:18:54.00,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Then, at the right time, I'll shove a stick so high up
Dialogue: 3,0:18:55.44,0:18:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}让那些该死的熊失去方向感
Dialogue: 2,0:18:55.44,0:18:57.60,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}that the bloody bears' balls will lose their bearings
